just_use telemetry.py

# label: EARLY (behaviorist-telemetry-v1)
# role: read-side for the human gesture telemetry table

Direct-SQLite reader for `lynrummy_elm_actions.gesture_metadata`.
The Elm client captures pointer paths during human drags and
posts them alongside each WireAction via the envelope shape
`{"action": ..., "gesture_metadata": ...}`. The server persists
the metadata verbatim in a sibling column. This module is the
Python read path.

## Relaxation of the CRUD-HTML rule

"CRUD HTML is agent interface" kept Python out of the DB for
gameplay (the forcing function was HTML simplicity; the benefit
was enumerate-and-bridge cross-checking between Elm and
Python). Telemetry is different: it's analysis data, not
gameplay data, and there's no bridge to enforce — Elm writes
and Python reads, nothing to agree on. HTTP would be wrapper
bureaucracy. Direct sqlite wins.

## Exposed surface

- `gesture_trail(session_id, *, db_path=None)` — generator of
  `(seq, action_kind, gesture_metadata_dict_or_None)` tuples,
  ordered by seq. `None` for non-drag actions AND for any
  row recorded before telemetry capture landed.
- `drag_summary(meta)` — collapse a metadata dict to
  `{n_points, duration_ms, start, end}`. Returns `None` for
  empty / absent metadata.
- CLI: `python3 telemetry.py <session_id> [seq]` — dump trail.

## DB path resolution

Reads `$GOPHER_DB` env var first, falls back to
`~/AngryGopher/prod/gopher.db`. The `db_path` kwarg on
`gesture_trail` overrides both (tests / demo DB / stress DB).

## Schema contract

Depends on `lynrummy_elm_actions` columns:
`session_id`, `seq`, `action_kind`, `gesture_metadata` (TEXT NULL).
Any schema rename requires updating this file — there's no
HTTP layer abstracting the column names.

## Future hooks

When telemetry broadens beyond drags (click timings, undo
events, hint interactions), the `gesture_metadata` JSON will
gain sibling keys inside the same column. Add per-kind
decoders here as they land; keep `drag_summary`-style
collapsers at this module level.

## Pointers

- Depends on: Python 3 stdlib only (`sqlite3`, `json`, `os`,
  `sys`). No `requests`, no `bs4` — direct DB.
- Producers: Elm client buffers gesture path during drag and
  flushes at `handleMouseUp` via `Main.Wire.sendAction`'s
  envelope; server persists in `views/lynrummy_elm.go`
  `lynrummyElmActions`.
